don't bother paying for fancy courses...<br>
get a couple good books with the kana tables and some kanji...make sure you have access to the net...<br>
The speaking you'll pick up as you go...most students by the college level know quite a bit of english...and would probably be glad to help you if you teach them some more english...<br>
<br>
*Point and talk slow*<br>
<br>
yup that's very very important...remember it well...you'll be doing it a lot...<br>
go to a store and pick up something with a lot of katakana on it...it's easiest to pick up because it's just butched english usually...car dealerships are awesome for that...go and get a stack of brochures...almost all the descriptions are in katakana...if you're good with cars you'll have no trouble and be fascinated by the depth of the brochures...(torque curves and transmission graphs...everything)<br>
then try and relate the katakana to hirigana...that's tricky...<br>
in about 3 months you should be able to read everything but kanji<br>
Kanji...well don't bother...give up...to learn enough to make the 6th grade level in 10 months is probably futile...just pick up the ones you see often...especially for identifying what bathroom to go in...NEVER make that mistake...study those very carefully <p><pre>
